The paper proposes a novel screening rule for multi-task feature learning, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" in computer science. The paper specifically deals with the problem of high-dimensional data, which suggests that it may fall under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) or "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of solvers and optimization techniques, which are common in "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multiple data matrices, which suggests that it may also fall under "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) sub-category.
